hopobject.body: Could I have a statement, please? prosvent best price Deregulation was meant to give consumers more choice and cheaper energy. Since the end of the Nineties we have in fact managed to reward and subsidise the most expensive, least flexible sources of energy while shrinking the number of participants to the big six. Some of this was on Ed Miliband’s watch as energy minister, so hearing him talk about capping prices fills me with despair.
